OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FIt is warned that the continuing
OL,8,Funcertainty over the war in the Middle
OL,9,FEast means interest rates could soon
OL,10,Frise as a result of the building wave
OL,11,Fof inflation, as ITV News Business and
OL,12,FEconomics Editor Joel Hills reports
OL,14,FIran has isolated its economy from
OL,15,Fmuch of the Western world, but the US
OL,16,Fand Israel's decision to start bombing
OL,17,Fit has unleashed devastating economic
OL,18,Fconsequences.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FOil and gas prices have surged, and a
OL,8,Fwave of inflation is building.
OL,9,FMeanwhile, the Strait of Hormuz is
OL,10,Fstill closed, and President Trump
OL,11,Ftalks of an extended blockade.
OL,13,FIn the UK, petrol and diesel prices
OL,14,Fhave already risen, along with
OL,15,Fmortgage rates.
OL,17,FPeople seem aware that their energy
OL,18,Fbills are going up later in the
OL,19,Fsummer, and food manufacturers are
OL,20,Fwarning food inflation will likely hit
OL,21,F10% by Christmas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FWe're in that strange moment between
OL,8,Fshock and full impact. The scale of
OL,9,Fwhat's coming is unknowable, but the
OL,10,Feffects of higher prices and shortages
OL,11,Fof oil and related petrochemicals all
OL,12,Flie ahead of us.
OL,14,FAmid the uncertainty, the Bank of
OL,15,FEngland has decided to wait and see -
OL,16,Fholding interest rates at 3.75% while
OL,17,Fsignalling that the next move is
OL,18,Flikely to be up.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,F"The war in the Middle East is causing
OL,8,Finflation to rise again this year,"
OL,9,Fsays Andrew Bailey, Governor of the
OL,10,FBank of England.
OL,12,F"We'll continue to monitor the
OL,13,Fsituation and its impact on the UK
OL,14,Feconomy very closely. Whatever
OL,15,Fhappens, our job is to make sure that
OL,16,Finflation gets back to the 2% target
OL,17,Fafter the initial impact of the war on
OL,18,Fenergy prices has passed."
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@cO]tD@AOUzD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FThe longer the conflict drags on, the
OL,8,Fhigher energy prices get, the bigger
OL,9,Fthe inflation shock, and the greater
OL,10,Fthe economic damage.
OL,12,FWho knows what will happen next? Amid
OL,13,Fso much uncertainty, the Bank has
OL,14,Fabandoned its traditional central
OL,15,Fforecast - an assessment of the most
OL,16,Flikely path for inflation, economic
OL,17,Fgrowth, and unemployment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FInstead, it publishes three scenarios
OL,8,F- which vary according to the price of
OL,9,Fenergy and how households and
OL,10,Fbusinesses react to yet another
OL,11,Fsqueeze on their living standards.
OL,13,FIn two of the three scenarios, the
OL,14,FBank raises interest rates as
OL,15,Fbusinesses seek to increase their
OL,16,Fprices and workers demand higher pay.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FIn Scenario C - the worst - Bank Rate
OL,8,Frises sharply to 5.25% at the
OL,9,Fbeginning of next year, as the
OL,10,Fheadline annual rate of inflation
OL,11,Fpeaks at 6.2% and the number of people
OL,12,Funemployed rises by 300,000 to 2.1
OL,13,Fmillion.
OL,15,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,16,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,17,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,18,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FThis scenario is built on the market
OL,8,Fprice of oil remaining above $120 a
OL,9,Fbarrel - broadly where we are this
OL,10,Fmorning - for the rest of the year.
OL,12,FAnd natural gas prices averaging 210p
OL,13,Fper therm - significantly higher than
OL,14,Fthe current level.
OL,16,FIn none of the Bank's scenarios does
OL,17,Fthe economy fall into a technical
OL,18,Frecession (in which the economy
OL,19,Fcontracts for a six-month period); in
OL,20,Fall of them, the outlook is one of
OL,21,Fgrindingly low growth.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FTo a greater or lesser extent, people
OL,8,Fare set to lose their jobs, and we
OL,9,Fwill feel poorer.
OL,11,FNot so long ago, the Bank was
OL,12,Fsignalling that the cost of borrowing
OL,13,Flooked set to fall. War has changed
OL,14,Feverything, and cuts are now off the
OL,15,Ftable.
OL,17,FIs wait and see the right approach?
OL,19,FOne member of the Monetary Policy
OL,20,FCommittee, Huw Pill, wants to begin
OL,21,Fhiking now.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1777648265
OL,3,CBank holds but hints interest set to
OL,4,Crise to contain inflation unleashed by
OL,5,Cwar
OL,7,FIn his view, the risks are one-sided,
OL,8,Fand the right thing to do is assume
OL,9,Fthe worst rather than just hope for
OL,10,Fthe best.
OL,12,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,13,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,14,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,15,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,16,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,17,Fbelow...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
